PRESCRIBED TEXTS
The text for 2010 is the 8th edition with the Auditing Clarity Standards Update booklet. The handbook is the 2011 edition. As there are substantial changes in the new editions, please do not purchase or rely on previous editions.

BLACKBOARD SITE
Please consult the e-learning Blackboard site for this course. The Blackboard site will provide you with copies of the class slides, learning guide for each topic, tutorial material and online assessment.It is the student's responsibility to attend classes and consult designated notice boards and websites for correct and up-to-date information regarding the course.

USING LEARNING RESOURCES
To study each Topic, you should:

Read assigned material before lectures/discussions;

attend the lectures/discussions ;

make writing part of your study habits;

access the resources on the course website ;

attempt the online tests and other textbook resources on the textbook website;

prepare for, attend and participate in the seminars; and

develop study groups to question and discuss audit issues outside of class and to prepare for class.

The lecture/discussions will introduce you to, and provide you with an overview of, the material covered in the relevant Topic. It is not necessary that you try to write down everything the lecturer has to say: the material is available elsewhere. It is more important that you read assigned materials in advance; listen and try to understand materials, fully engage in discussions, and raise questions about items you do not understand ; in order to construct a solid foundation upon which you will build your subsequent learning of the Topic.

